caption: Thought the Green Farm taco was great, loved the tai peanut sauce. Had the steak tacos also, our daughter thinks they "smack".  If you're thinking traditional Mexican tacos with 3 ingredients, then maybe Pilsen is for you.  American Mexican food, Taco Bell (which sometimes is what I'm looking for).  Something new with creative combinations, Takito Street. This is upscale culinary, it is what it is.  People pay $45 for a hamburger so $4 for a taco isn't a bad deal. I don't drink, but the descriptions of the drinks makes me want to start again!

Food is not good - poor execution, odd flavors, was only given 2 tortillas for an entire skirt steak platter. $10 for a 6oz margarita. Overpriced and underwhelming. Avoid this place if you like quality Mexican food.

Terrible service, waited an hour for every drink order. Horrifically overpriced as well we paid 300 for margs and tacos for 6. They also had one poor girl serving over half the restaurant which screamed bad management

Horrible experience, over priced,small portions. I called to make sure they had everything on the menu, Katelyn assured me you did, that was a lie. No updated menus I wasn't sure how to use the app to download the menu and neither did our server what a joke. I wanted Korean tacos they said not today then the server came back and said yes they do have it, he lied and brought me barbacoa. Ordered drinks they didn't have the alcohol for the drink, no strawberries for my drink. Server was running up and back to the kitchen because he had no idea what was and wasn't available on the menu. It was my birthday celebration turned nightmare. Shame on you owner and train your staff.
Food was bland. Tacos across the street are way better especially the  Al Pastor tacos.

Update: Their menu changed and so my review: none of the interesting/good tacos are left on the menu. Food is tasteless, gone are spices and flavours. Will NOT go back, will not recommend!  Place has potential, but need to be more consistent. When you decide to order one more taco because it was delicious then place deserves five stars. You  expect that extra taco to be equally tasty especially if is the same kind. So when you get something that even better you're generally more happy. That is until you realize that what was served to you before was half full taco. My advise is to order fewer tacos and order more later. Otherwise they might make them smaller just to make them fit into paper tray.

Food was bland (I got the el pastor tacos), small, and overpriced. Went for brunch and wanted to get one of the brunch options but everything was so basic - no meat on the chilaquiles or burrito, no egg or protein on the avocado toast, etc, so I went with the tacos which came with a stale tasting corn tortilla. Service was meh. Ambiance and decor is okay at least.

I was not happy with my experience at takito street. The food was tasteless expensive and served very small portions. The service was also quite poor: they forgot part of our order! Will not be returning and definitely wouldn't suggest it to people. There are many better Mexican places in Lincoln Park.
Food was flavourless, the waiter forgot one of our 5 total orders and seemed offended when we told him the food wasn't great, portions were so small and food was WAY over priced. DO NOT RECOMMEND
The food was flavorless and overpriced. They forgot some of our order. And did I mention the prices were insane. DO NOT GET THE TACOS AL PASTOR. Would not go back!
The food is not good, pretty sure the fish tacos are frozen fish sticks warmed up. Staff was nice and attentive but would not go back.
